  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🩸 Gestational Diabetes Risk — Model Training\n",
    "**MedPredict | JSS STU | Dept. of CS&E | Academic Year 2025-26**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "### Pipeline\n",
    "1. Load & explore the Pima Indians Diabetes Dataset\n",
    "2. Data cleaning & zero-imputation\n",
    "3. Feature engineering → 30 features\n",
    "4. Train/test split + SMOTETomek balancing\n",
    "5. Model comparison (LightGBM, XGBoost, Random Forest, Stacking)\n",
    "6. Optuna hyperparameter tuning on best model\n",
    "7. Evaluation: Accuracy, Macro F1, per-class report, 10-Fold CV\n",
    "8. Save model + scaler → `model/gdm_model.sav`, `model/gdm_scaler.sav`\n",
    "9. Integration snippet for `app.py`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset:** Pima Indians Diabetes Dataset (UCI / Kaggle)  \n",
    "**Target:** `Outcome` (0 = No GDM, 1 = GDM)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run once\n",
    "!pip install lightgbm xgboost optuna imbalanced-learn scikit-learn pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn shap --quiet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports & Config"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, pickle, warnings\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold, cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix,\n",
    "    f1_score, roc_auc_score\n",
    ")\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, StackingClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "import lightgbm as lgb\n",
    "import xgboost as xgb\n",
    "import optuna\n",
    "from imblearn.combine import SMOTETomek\n",
    "\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "optuna.logging.set_verbosity(optuna.logging.WARNING)\n",
    "SEED = 42\n",
    "os.makedirs('model', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "print('✅ All imports successful')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option A — Automatic download from URL (recommended)**  \n",
    "**Option B — Manual upload** if you already have `diabetes.csv`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Option A: Auto-download ──────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "\n",
    "url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jbrownlee/Datasets/master/pima-indians-diabetes.data.csv'\n",
    "columns = [\n",
    "    'Pregnancies', 'Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness',\n",
    "    'Insulin', 'BMI', 'DiabetesPedigree', 'Age', 'Outcome'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "urllib.request.urlretrieve(url, 'diabetes.csv')\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('diabetes.csv', header=None, names=columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Option B: Manual ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# df = pd.read_csv('diabetes.csv')   # uncomment if uploading manually\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Shape: {df.shape}')\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. EDA & Data Cleaning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('=== Basic Info ===')\n",
    "print(df.info())\n",
    "print('\\n=== Describe ===')\n",
    "df.describe().T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('=== Class Distribution ===')\n",
    "print(df['Outcome'].value_counts())\n",
    "print(f\"\\nClass balance: {df['Outcome'].mean()*100:.1f}% positive (GDM)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "df['Outcome'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0], color=['#10B981','#EC4899'])\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Class Distribution')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xticklabels(['No GDM (0)', 'GDM (1)'], rotation=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Correlation heatmap\n",
    "corr = df.corr()\n",
    "sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='RdPu', ax=axes[1], cbar=True)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Feature Correlation Matrix')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Zero-value imputation ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Biologically impossible zero values in these columns → replace with median\n",
    "zero_impute_cols = ['Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness', 'Insulin', 'BMI']\n",
    "\n",
    "for col in zero_impute_cols:\n",
    "    n_zeros = (df[col] == 0).sum()\n",
    "    median_val = df[df[col] != 0][col].median()\n",
    "    df[col] = df[col].replace(0, median_val)\n",
    "    print(f'{col}: {n_zeros} zeros replaced with median {median_val:.2f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\n✅ Zero imputation complete')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Feature Engineering (30 Features)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def engineer_gdm_features(df):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Matches the engineer_gdm_features() function in app.py exactly.\"\"\"\n",
    "    d = df.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Raw features (8) ===\n",
    "    # Already present: Pregnancies, Glucose, BloodPressure, SkinThickness,\n",
    "    #                  Insulin, BMI, DiabetesPedigree, Age\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Clinical threshold flags (8) ===\n",
    "    d['HighGlucose']         = (d['Glucose'] >= 140).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['VeryHighGlucose']     = (d['Glucose'] >= 200).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['Obese']               = (d['BMI'] >= 30).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['Overweight']          = ((d['BMI'] >= 25) & (d['BMI'] < 30)).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['HighInsulin']         = (d['Insulin'] > 166).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['HighBP']              = (d['BloodPressure'] > 90).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['ElderlyMother']       = (d['Age'] > 35).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['MultiParity']         = (d['Pregnancies'] >= 3).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Interaction & derived features (7) ===\n",
    "    d['GlucoseBMI']          = d['Glucose'] * d['BMI'] / 100\n",
    "    d['GlucoseAge']          = d['Glucose'] * d['Age'] / 100\n",
    "    d['InsulinGlucoseRatio'] = d['Insulin'] / (d['Glucose'] + 1e-6)\n",
    "    d['BMIAge']              = d['BMI'] * d['Age'] / 100\n",
    "    d['PregnancyAge']        = d['Pregnancies'] * d['Age']\n",
    "    d['PedigreeAge']         = d['DiabetesPedigree'] * d['Age']\n",
    "    d['GlucoseInsulin']      = d['Glucose'] * d['Insulin'] / 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Categorical encodings (3) ===\n",
    "    d['GlucoseCategory']     = pd.cut(d['Glucose'], bins=[0,99,125,999],\n",
    "                                       labels=[0,1,2]).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['BMICategory']         = pd.cut(d['BMI'], bins=[0,18.4,24.9,29.9,999],\n",
    "                                       labels=[0,1,2,3]).astype(int)\n",
    "    d['InsulinResistance']   = ((d['Glucose'] > 140) & (d['Insulin'] > 166)).astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Risk scores (2) ===\n",
    "    d['MetabolicRisk']       = (d['HighGlucose'] + d['Obese'] + d['HighBP'] + d['HighInsulin'])\n",
    "    d['RiskScore']           = (d['HighGlucose'] + d['Obese'] + d['HighBP'] +\n",
    "                                d['ElderlyMother'] + d['MultiParity'] +\n",
    "                                (d['DiabetesPedigree'] > 0.5).astype(int))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # === Physiological markers (2) ===\n",
    "    d['HOMA_IR']             = (d['Glucose'] * d['Insulin']) / 405\n",
    "    d['SkinBMIRatio']        = d['SkinThickness'] / (d['BMI'] + 1e-6)\n",
    "\n",
    "    return d\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df_feat = engineer_gdm_features(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "FEATURE_COLS = [\n",
    "    'Pregnancies', 'Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness',\n",
    "    'Insulin', 'BMI', 'DiabetesPedigree', 'Age',\n",
    "    'HighGlucose', 'VeryHighGlucose', 'Obese', 'Overweight',\n",
    "    'HighInsulin', 'HighBP', 'ElderlyMother', 'MultiParity',\n",
    "    'GlucoseBMI', 'GlucoseAge', 'InsulinGlucoseRatio',\n",
    "    'BMIAge', 'PregnancyAge', 'PedigreeAge', 'GlucoseInsulin',\n",
    "    'GlucoseCategory', 'BMICategory', 'InsulinResistance',\n",
    "    'MetabolicRisk', 'RiskScore', 'HOMA_IR', 'SkinBMIRatio'\n",
    "]\n",
    "TARGET_COL = 'Outcome'\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df_feat[FEATURE_COLS].values\n",
    "y = df_feat[TARGET_COL].values\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Feature matrix shape: {X.shape}  ({len(FEATURE_COLS)} features)')\n",
    "print(f'Target shape: {y.shape}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Train/Test Split + Balancing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scale\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_sc = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_sc  = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SMOTETomek only on training data (no leakage)\n",
    "smt = SMOTETomek(random_state=SEED)\n",
    "X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smt.fit_resample(X_train_sc, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Train before balancing: {np.bincount(y_train)}')\n",
    "print(f'Train after  balancing: {np.bincount(y_train_bal)}')\n",
    "print(f'Test  (untouched):      {np.bincount(y_test)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Baseline Model Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_models = {\n",
    "    'Random Forest':  RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED),\n",
    "    'LightGBM':       lgb.LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED, verbose=-1),\n",
    "    'XGBoost':        xgb.XGBClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED,\n",
    "                                         use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss'),\n",
    "    'Grad. Boosting': GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "for name, model in baseline_models.items():\n",
    "    model.fit(X_train_bal, y_train_bal)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_sc)\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred) * 100\n",
    "    f1  = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro') * 100\n",
    "    results.append({'Model': name, 'Accuracy (%)': round(acc,2), 'Macro F1 (%)': round(f1,2)})\n",
    "    print(f'{name:<22} Acc={acc:.2f}%  Macro-F1={f1:.2f}%')\n",
    "\n",
    "results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('Macro F1 (%)', ascending=False)\n",
    "print('\\n', results_df.to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Optuna Hyperparameter Tuning (LightGBM)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def objective_gdm(trial):\n",
    "    params = {\n",
    "        'n_estimators':      trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 100, 600),\n",
    "        'learning_rate':     trial.suggest_float('learning_rate', 0.01, 0.3, log=True),\n",
    "        'num_leaves':        trial.suggest_int('num_leaves', 15, 127),\n",
    "        'max_depth':         trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 3, 12),\n",
    "        'min_child_samples': trial.suggest_int('min_child_samples', 5, 50),\n",
    "        'subsample':         trial.suggest_float('subsample', 0.5, 1.0),\n",
    "        'colsample_bytree':  trial.suggest_float('colsample_bytree', 0.5, 1.0),\n",
    "        'reg_alpha':         trial.suggest_float('reg_alpha', 1e-4, 1.0, log=True),\n",
    "        'reg_lambda':        trial.suggest_float('reg_lambda', 1e-4, 1.0, log=True),\n",
    "        'random_state': 42, 'verbose': -1\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(**params)\n",
    "    cv    = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n",
    "    score = cross_val_score(model, X_train_bal, y_train_bal,\n",
    "                            cv=cv, scoring='f1_macro').mean()\n",
    "    return score\n",
    "\n",
    "study_gdm = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize')\n",
    "study_gdm.optimize(objective_gdm, n_trials=100, show_progress_bar=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nBest Macro F1 (CV): {study_gdm.best_value*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "print(f'Best params: {study_gdm.best_params}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Final Model Training"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "best_params_gdm = study_gdm.best_params\n",
    "best_params_gdm['random_state'] = SEED\n",
    "best_params_gdm['verbose'] = -1\n",
    "\n",
    "gdm_model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(**best_params_gdm)\n",
    "gdm_model.fit(X_train_bal, y_train_bal)\n",
    "\n",
    "y_pred_gdm = gdm_model.predict(X_test_sc)\n",
    "y_prob_gdm = gdm_model.predict_proba(X_test_sc)[:, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== TEST SET RESULTS ===')\n",
    "print(f'Accuracy : {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_gdm)*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "print(f'Macro F1 : {f1_score(y_test, y_pred_gdm, average=\"macro\")*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "print(f'ROC-AUC  : {roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob_gdm)*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "print('\\nClassification Report:')\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_gdm, target_names=['No GDM', 'GDM']))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Confusion Matrix\n",
    "cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_gdm)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='RdPu',\n",
    "            xticklabels=['No GDM', 'GDM'],\n",
    "            yticklabels=['No GDM', 'GDM'], ax=ax)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Confusion Matrix — GDM Model', fontsize=14, color='#9D174D')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Actual')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Predicted')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Cross-Validation (10-Fold)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cv10 = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\n",
    "cv_scores = cross_val_score(gdm_model, X_train_bal, y_train_bal,\n",
    "                             cv=cv10, scoring='accuracy')\n",
    "print(f'10-Fold CV Accuracy: {cv_scores.mean()*100:.2f}% ± {cv_scores.std()*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "print(f'Min: {cv_scores.min()*100:.2f}%  |  Max: {cv_scores.max()*100:.2f}%')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Feature Importance (SHAP)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import shap\n",
    "\n",
    "explainer_gdm = shap.TreeExplainer(gdm_model)\n",
    "shap_values   = explainer_gdm.shap_values(X_test_sc)\n",
    "\n",
    "# For binary SHAP: shap_values is list of 2 arrays; use class 1\n",
    "sv = shap_values[1] if isinstance(shap_values, list) else shap_values\n",
    "\n",
    "shap.summary_plot(sv, X_test_sc, feature_names=FEATURE_COLS, show=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. Save Model & Scaler"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pickle.dump(gdm_model,  open('model/gdm_model.sav', 'wb'))\n",
    "pickle.dump(scaler,     open('model/gdm_scaler.sav', 'wb'))\n",
    "pickle.dump(FEATURE_COLS, open('model/gdm_feature_names.sav', 'wb'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Saved:')\n",
    "print('   model/gdm_model.sav')\n",
    "print('   model/gdm_scaler.sav')\n",
    "print('   model/gdm_feature_names.sav')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 12. app.py Integration Snippet\n",
    "\n",
    "Paste this into `app.py` to replace the rule-based function:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "snippet = '''\n",
    "# ── In app.py load_models() ───────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "gdm_model  = pickle.load(open(\"model/gdm_model.sav\",  \"rb\"))\n",
    "gdm_scaler = pickle.load(open(\"model/gdm_scaler.sav\", \"rb\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Replace predict_gdm_rule_based() with this ───────────────────────\n",
    "def predict_gdm_model(pregnancies, glucose, bp, skin_thick,\n",
    "                       insulin, bmi, pedigree, age):\n",
    "    features = engineer_gdm_features(\n",
    "        pregnancies, glucose, bp, skin_thick, insulin, bmi, pedigree, age\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    features_scaled = gdm_scaler.transform(features)\n",
    "    prediction      = gdm_model.predict(features_scaled)[0]\n",
    "    probs           = gdm_model.predict_proba(features_scaled)[0]\n",
    "    confidence      = max(probs) * 100\n",
    "    # Map binary (0/1) → 3-level display (0=Low, 1=Moderate, 2=High)\n",
    "    risk_level = 0 if prediction == 0 else (1 if probs[1] < 0.75 else 2)\n",
    "    return risk_level, confidence, []\n",
    "'''\n",
    "print(snippet)"
   ]
  },
  {
